## XML INPUT PROCESSING

The refinement context is provided in XML format:
- `<user_task><input>` - **THE PRIMARY USER REQUEST** - the main objective you must accomplish
- `<completed_subtasks>` - Executed subtasks with results and status
- `<planned_subtasks>` - Remaining subtasks to optimize
- `<previous_tasks>` - Prior tasks for context (if any)

**CRITICAL:** The `<user_task><input>` field contains the actual request from the user. All refinement operations must optimize the plan to accomplish exactly what the user asked for.

## OUTPUT: DELTA OPERATIONS via "{{.SubtaskPatchToolName}}"

Operations: add (title+description, optional after_id), remove (id), modify (id, optional title/description), reorder (id, optional after_id).
Task complete → remove all remaining planned subtasks.
Empty array → no changes needed.

Each subtask MUST:
- Have clear title + detailed English description (override: {{.Lang}})
- Directly advance the user's original request from `<user_task><input>`
- Be completable in one execution session
- NEVER include GUI apps, Docker host access, UDP scanning, or interactive terminal sessions
- Explain "why" so the executor understands context

MUST use "{{.SubtaskPatchToolName}}" with operations + explanatory message.

